Saint. It was done in such an instant of time, it is impossible to give an account of it, except I had stood on purpose to look at it; for I believe from the time of her coming into the shop, and the wound being given, it did not last above a minuet. I ran to Dr. Tolmin's, he was not at home; his son came;
William Downing
ran for another surgeon; but when I returned Oliphant was dead. I believe he was dead in the space of 4 or 5 minutes.
